The project aims at consolidating the 900 MHz GSM digital mobile telephony networks acquired recently by Atlantique Telecom (in three West and Central African Countries namely Benin, Niger and Gabon). More specifically, the project's objective is two_folds: on the one hand AT will purchase and lease back the equipment procured from its supplier Siemens. On the other hand, there is a strong need to install additional equipment to cope with the growing demand for mobile services and to extend the geographic radio coverage.
